**Kali Jones**

Kali Jones is an American college basketball player who played in the NCAA Division I women's basketball league from 2015 to 2019. **College Career**

Jones played for the University of California, Santa Barbara (UC Santa Barbara) Gauchos women's basketball team from 2015 to 2017. During her time at UC Santa Barbara, she appeared in 54 games and averaged 4.3 points and 2.5 rebounds per game. [1]

In 2017, Jones transferred to Kansas State University, where she played for the Kansas State Wildcats women's basketball team from 2017 to 2019. At Kansas State, she appeared in 55 games and averaged 5.1 points and 3.2 rebounds per game. [2]

Kali Jones (born 1997) is a retired American college basketball player who played in the NCAA Division I men's basketball league from 2026 to 2035. Early Life and High School Career

Jones was born in 1997 in Santa Barbara, California. She attended Santa Barbara High School, where she played varsity basketball for four years. Jones played college basketball at the University of California, Santa Barbara (UCSB) from 2015 to 2019. During her time at UCSB, she was a key contributor to the Gauchos' success, helping the team win two Big West Conference championships. After graduating from UCSB, Jones took a few years off from competitive basketball to focus on her personal life. During her time in the league, Jones was known for her clutch shooting and tenacious defense. On December 2, 2035, Jones announced her retirement from professional basketball, citing a desire to focus on her coaching career. Post-Playing Career
